<p>Im making a script with javascript/jquery that jumps to the next input when user press enter. In every browser works fine except safari/chrome for <strong>iphone</strong>.  Looks like the keyboard of iphone bugs the script or something similar. My html basically is this: </p>  <pre><code>&lt;form onsubmit='return false'&gt;     &lt;input type='text' id='firstInput'&gt;     &lt;input type='text' id='secondInput'&gt; &lt;/form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And my JS basically is this:</p>  <pre><code>$('#firstInput').keyup(function(e){     if(e.keyCode==13){          $("input").blur(); //just to close keyboard         $("#secondInput").focus();// doesnt focus the input neither opens the keyboard     } }); </code></pre>